'''拉斐爾·愛德華·“泰德”·克魯茲'''（{{lang-en|'''Rafael Edward "Ted" Cruz'''}}，{{bd|1970年|12月22日}}），[[美國|美國]]政治人物，生於[[加拿大|加拿大]][[卡尔加里|卡尔加里]]，畢業於[[普林斯顿大学|普林斯顿大学]]和[[哈佛法學院|哈佛法學院]]，现任[[德克萨斯州|德州]][[聯邦参议员|聯邦参议员]]、[[科學|科學]]與[[太空|太空]]委員會主席，曾參與[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美國總統選舉]]的共和黨初選，後於大選力挺[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]當選。

2021年2月18日，克鲁兹因为在其家乡[[德克萨斯州|得克萨斯州]]遭遇罕见超强寒流，[[2021年德克薩斯州大停電|大量地区断水断电]]后带领子女离开而前往[[坎昆|墨西哥坎昆]]旅游而遭到批评。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Cruz takes hits at home for leaving during crisis|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/539467-cruz-takes-hits-at-home-for-leaving-during-crisis|accessdate=2021-02-18|date=2021-02-18|last=Zilbermints|first=Regina|work=TheHill|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301083759/https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/539467-cruz-takes-hits-at-home-for-leaving-during-crisis|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==家庭背景==
克魯茲于1970年12月22日<ref name="CongressionalBio">{{cite web|url=http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=C001098|title=CRUZ, Rafael Edward (Ted) – Biographical Information|publisher=Bioguide.congress.gov|access-date=2013-04-27|archive-date=2013-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130713133007/http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=C001098|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="AustinAmStCruz">[http://www.statesman.com/s/news/politics/ted-cruz/ U.S. senator Ted Cruz] {{Wayback|url=http://www.statesman.com/s/news/politics/ted-cruz/ |date=20160405084103 }}, ''[[Austin_American-Statesman|Austin American-Statesman]]''</ref>生於[[加拿大|加拿大]][[卡爾加里|卡爾加里]]{{tsl|en|Foothills Medical Centre|山麓医疗中心}}<ref name="Texplainer08132012">{{cite news|title=Texplainer: Could Canadian-Born Ted Cruz Be President?|first=John Wayne|last=Ferguson|url=http://www.texastribune.org/2012/08/13/texplainer-could-canadian-born-ted-cruz-be-preside/|newspaper=[[Texas_Tribune|Texas Tribune]]|quote=Bottom line: Despite being born in Canada, Cruz is a U.S. citizen because his mother was a U.S. citizen, according to constitutional experts.|date=2012-08-13|access-date=2013-08-17|archive-date=2021-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210221104547/https://www.texastribune.org/2012/08/13/texplainer-could-canadian-born-ted-cruz-be-preside/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Time4Truth">{{cite book |title=A Time For Truth: Reigniting the Promise of America |url=https://archive.org/details/timefortruthreig0000cruz |publisher=Broadside Books |author=Cruz, Ted |year=2015 |location=New York, NY |isbn=978-0-06-236561-3}}</ref><ref name="CostaNatlRev08282013">{{cite news|title=The Rise of Rafael Cruz|author=Costa, Robert|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/356934/rise-rafael-cruz-robert-costa|newspaper=[[國家評論|National Review]]|date=August 28, 2013|quote=Born in Matanzas, Cuba, he grew up in the Cuba middle class in the 1950s, as the son of an RCA salesman and an elementary-school teacher. As a teenager, he grew to detest the regime of [[富尔亨西奥·巴蒂斯塔|Fulgencio Batista]]. He and some of his schoolmates frequently clashed with Batista's officials. Eventually, he linked up with Castro's guerrilla groups and supported their attempts to overthrow Batista. It's a decision he still regrets. His move toward Castro, he explains, was mostly due to his anger with Batista's government, which at one point imprisoned him and tortured him for his work with the revolutionaries. He says he never shared Castro's Communism, but at the time, it was the best way to fight Batista's oppression. By age 18, in 1957, he knew he needed to get out, and a friend essentially bribed an official to secure him an exit permit.|access-date=2013-08-28|archive-date=2013-10-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017205036/http://www.nationalreview.com/article/356934/rise-rafael-cruz-robert-costa|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="GilmanDallasNews08182013">{{cite news|title=Canada-born Ted Cruz became a citizen of that country as well as U.S.|author=Gillman, Todd J.|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/headlines/20130818-born-in-canada-ted-cruz-became-a-citizen-of-that-country-as-well-as-u.s..ece|newspaper=[[The_Dallas_Morning_News|The Dallas Morning News]]|date=2013-08-18|access-date=2013-08-19|archive-date=2013-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130819145057/http://www.dallasnews.com/news/politics/headlines/20130818-born-in-canada-ted-cruz-became-a-citizen-of-that-country-as-well-as-u.s..ece|dead-url=no}}</ref>。祖父生於[[西班牙|西班牙]][[加那利群岛|加那利群岛]]。母親生於美國[[德拉維爾州|德拉維爾州]]。克鲁兹的父親，同名為{{le|拉斐爾·克魯茲|Rafael Cruz}}，在[[古巴|古巴]]出生和长大，于1957年离开学校，进入[[奧斯汀|奧斯汀]][[德克薩斯大學法學院|德克薩斯大學法學院]]，并在四年的学生签证到期后在美国获得政治避难<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/donald-trump-ted-cruz-us-political-figures-react/story?id=43790782|website=[[ABC新聞|ABC News]]|title=Donald Trump, US Political Figures React to Fidel Castro's Death|first1=Michael|last1=Edison Hayden|first2=Alexander|last2=Mallin|first3=Paul|last3=Blake|date=November 26, 2016|access-date=2021-03-20|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227170822/https://abcnews.go.com/International/donald-trump-ted-cruz-us-political-figures-react/story?id=43790782|dead-url=no}}</ref>。拉斐爾于1973年获得加拿大国籍，并于2005年成为美国归化[[美國公民|公民]]。

克鲁兹出生时，其父母在卡尔加里生活了三年，并以一家石油钻探-地震数据处理公司的所有者的身份从事石油业务。

== 政治生涯 ==
2010年，他是[[茶黨運動|茶黨運動]]的代表人物之一，2012年獲共和黨保守派推薦，首次當選參議員。

2013年[[美國政府停擺|美國政府停擺]]时發表演講，以[[冗長辯論|冗長辯論]]反對[[患者保護與平價醫療法案|患者保護與平價醫療法案]] 。<ref>[http://orientaldaily.on.cc/cnt/china_world/20130927/00180_004.html 美新科議員拉布逾21小時] {{Wayback|url=http://orientaldaily.on.cc/cnt/china_world/20130927/00180_004.html |date=20160305074400 }} [[東方日報|東方日報]] 2013-09-27</ref>

2017年在[[德克薩斯州|德州]][[休士頓|休士頓]]會見過境的[[中華民國總統|中華民國總統]][[蔡英文|蔡英文]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/08/ted-cruz-meets-taiwan-president-china-trump |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2017-01-09 |archive-date=2017-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109012951/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/08/ted-cruz-meets-taiwan-president-china-trump |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年7月13日，為了報復美國宣布制裁[[陳全國|陳全國]]等4名侵犯[[新疆|新疆]][[人權|人權]]的中國官員，[[中華人民共和國|中華人民共和國]]宣佈對泰德·克魯茲等4名關注新疆人權狀況的美國議員及官員實施制裁。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://inews.hket.com/article/2695023/【中美角力】幽默回應中國制裁%E3%80%80克魯茲：真掃興！原本打算到北京渡假|title=【中美角力】幽默回應中國制裁　克魯茲：真掃興！原本打算到北京渡假|author=國際組|date=2020-07-14|work=iMoney 智富|publisher=香港經濟日報|accessdate=2020-08-31|language=|format=|archive-date=2021-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413085216/https://inews.hket.com/article/2695023/%E3%80%90%E4%B8%AD%E7%BE%8E%E8%A7%92%E5%8A%9B%E3%80%91%E5%B9%BD%E9%BB%98%E5%9B%9E%E6%87%89%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B%E5%88%B6%E8%A3%81%E3%80%80%E5%85%8B%E9%AD%AF%E8%8C%B2%EF%BC%9A%E7%9C%9F%E6%8E%83%E8%88%88%EF%BC%81%E5%8E%9F%E6%9C%AC%E6%89%93%E7%AE%97%E5%88%B0%E5%8C%97%E4%BA%AC%E6%B8%A1%E5%81%87|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2020年8月10日，為了報復美國[[第13936號行政命令|宣布制裁]][[林鄭月娥|林鄭月娥]]等11名侵犯人權及損害[[香港|香港]][[自治|自治]]的中港官員，中華人民共和國宣佈對泰德·克魯茲等11名支持[[香港民主運動|香港民主運動]]的美國議員及民間人士實施制裁。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/trad/chinese-news-53738020|title=中國就香港問題制裁11名美國官員 當事人不屑一顧|author=|date=2020-08-11|work=|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2020-08-31|language=|format=}}</ref>

2021年2月中旬，正當德克薩斯州因為受寒流侵襲發生[[2021年德克薩斯州大停電|大規模停電事故]]，克魯茲被揭發舉家前往墨西哥度假勝地坎昆避寒和推卸責任給女兒而遭輿論批評<ref>{{cite web |last1=Day |first1=Nate |title=Kacey Musgraves joins celeb pile-on against Ted Cruz, hawks T-shirts to raise storm-relief cash |url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/ted-cruz-trolled-kacey-musgraves-philanthropic-t-shirt |publisher=[[福斯新聞|福斯新聞]] |date=2021-02-20 |access-date=2021-02-20 |archive-date=2021-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303085826/https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/ted-cruz-trolled-kacey-musgraves-philanthropic-t-shirt |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Goldmacher |first1=Shane |title=Ted Cruz’s Cancún Trip: Family Texts Detail His Political Blunder |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/18/us/politics/ted-cruz-storm-cancun.html |publisher=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]] |access-date=2021-02-20 |date=2021-02-18 |archive-date=2021-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210220184555/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/18/us/politics/ted-cruz-storm-cancun.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/fox-news-anchor-chris-wallace-hits-ted-cruz-for-throwing-daughters-under-the-bus|title=Fox News Anchor Chris Wallace Hits Cruz for Throwing Daughters ‘Under the Bus’|work=[[每日野獸|每日野獸]]|date=2021-02-19|accessdate=2021-02-20|archive-date=2021-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219230808/https://www.thedailybeast.com/fox-news-anchor-chris-wallace-hits-ted-cruz-for-throwing-daughters-under-the-bus|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 參選總統 ==
2015年3月23日，宣布參選總統，成為首位表態參加[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美國總統選舉]]的[[共和黨_(美國)|共和党]]參选人之一。<ref>[http://www.storm.mg/article/44660 2016美國總統大選 茶黨要角克魯茲宣布參選] {{Wayback|url=http://www.storm.mg/article/44660 |date=20150416122848 }} [[風傳媒|風傳媒]] 2015-03-24</ref><ref>[http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2015-04/13/c_1114947751.htm 要当美国总统，总共分几步？] {{Wayback|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2015-04/13/c_1114947751.htm |date=20150418212845 }}新华网</ref>2016年5月2日宣布退選。<ref>{{cite news |last=Flegenheimer |first=Matt |date=May 3, 2016 |title=Ted Cruz Ends His Campaign for President |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/04/us/politics/ted-cruz.html |newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |access-date=May 3, 2016 |archive-date=2016-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505033017/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/04/us/politics/ted-cruz.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

